{% block content %}

<div class="wrapper">
  <h1 class="alpha">Boxes</h1>
</div>

<section class="panel panel--separated--top wrapper">
  <div class="grid-wrap">

    <div class="grid-col desktop-grid-one-third  tablet-grid-one-half ">
      <h2 class="delta">Box:</h2>
      <!---
      title: Standard box
      usage: |
        Boxes are components that can be used to visually compartmentalise different sections of the page.
        Their look can be extended in a number of ways to place emphasis on different areas of the page.
      -->
      <article class="box">
        <header class="box__header">
          <h3 class="gamma">
            Regional Gross Value Added (Income Approach)
          </h3>
        </header><!-- /box__header -->

        <div class="box__content">
          <ul class="list--bullet">
            <li>In 2012 the South East had the largest increase in GVA</li>
            <li>Between 1997 and 2011 the contribution of building to total GVA decreased in each of the NUTS1 regions. </li>
          </ul><!--  /list-bullet -->
        </div><!-- /box__content -->

        <footer class="box__footer box__actions">
          <a class="btn btn--primary btn--small btn--narrow" href="#">
            Download .xls
            <span class="icon icon-download icon--button-inline"></span>
          </a>
        </footer><!-- /box__actions -->
      </article><!-- /box -->
    </div>

    <div class="grid-col desktop-grid-one-third  tablet-grid-one-half ">
      <h2 class="delta">Padded box:</h2>
      <!--- title: Padded box -->
      <article class="box box--padded">
        <header class="box__header">
          <h3 class="gamma">
            Consumer Price Inflation
          </h3>
        </header><!-- /box__header -->
        <div class="box__content">
          <ul class="list--bullet">
            <li>The Consumer Prices Index (CPI) grew by 1.5%</li>
            <li>Falls in transport services costs, notably air fares</li>
          </ul><!--  /list-bullet -->
        </div><!-- /box__content -->
        <footer class="box__footer box__actions">
          <a class="btn btn--primary btn--small btn--narrow" href="#">
            Download .xls
            <span class="icon icon-download icon--button-inline"></span>
          </a>
        </footer>
      </article><!-- /box -->
    </div>

    <div class="grid-col desktop-grid-one-third  tablet-grid-one-half tablet-grid-clear ">
      <h2 class="delta">Sectioned box</h2>
      <!---
      title: Sectioned box
      usage: >
       Adds a border to the box class.
       To be used when the box sits on a white background.
      -->
      <article class="box sectioned">
        <header class="box__header">
          <h3 class="gamma">
            Regional Gross Value Added (Income Approach)
          </h3>
        </header><!-- /box__header -->

        <div class="box__content">
          <ul class="list--bullet">
            <li>In 2012 the South East had the largest increase in GVA</li>
            <li>Between 1997 and 2011 the contribution of building to total GVA decreased in each of the NUTS1 regions. </li>
          </ul><!--  /list-bullet -->

        </div><!-- /box__content -->
        <footer class="box__footer box__actions">
          <a class="btn btn--primary btn--small btn--narrow" href="#">
            Download .xls
            <span class="icon icon-download icon--button-inline"></span>
          </a>
        </footer>
      </article><!-- /box -->
    </div>

    <div class="grid-col desktop-grid-one-third tablet-grid-one-half ">
      <h2 class="delta">Lifted box</h2>
      <!---
      title: Lifted box
      devnotes: >
        Uses box-shadow, so comes with the normal CSS3 browser compatibility caveats.
        Don't rely solely on this to create a visual emphasis.
      usage: >
        Adds a drop-shadow to a box element.
        To be used when the box sits on a white background.
      -->
      <article class="box lifted">
        <header class="box__header">
          <h3 class="gamma">
            Regional Gross Value Added (Income Approach)
          </h3>
        </header><!-- /box__header -->

        <div class="box__content">
          <ul class="list--bullet">
            <li>In 2012 the South East had the largest increase in GVA</li>
            <li>Between 1997 and 2011 the contribution of building to total GVA decreased in each of the NUTS1 regions. </li>
          </ul><!--  /list-bullet -->

        </div><!-- /box__content -->
        <footer class="box__footer box__actions">
          <a class="btn btn--primary btn--small btn--narrow" href="#">
            Download .xls
            <span class="icon icon-download icon--button-inline"></span>
          </a>
        </footer>
      </article><!-- /box -->
    </div>

    <div class="grid-col desktop-grid-one-third  tablet-grid-one-half tablet-grid-clear">
      <h2 class="delta">Lifted, sectioned, and padded box</h2>
      <!---
      title: Combinations
      inline: Lifted, sectioned, and padded box
      devnotes: |
        Different combinations of classes can be used for different effects.
      -->

      <article class="box box--padded lifted sectioned">
        <header class="box__header">
          <h3 class="gamma">
            Regional Gross Value Added (Income Approach)
          </h3>
        </header><!-- /box__header -->

        <div class="box__content">
          <ul class="list--bullet">
            <li>In 2012 the South East had the largest increase in GVA</li>
            <li>Between 1997 and 2011 the contribution of building to total GVA decreased in each of the NUTS1 regions. </li>
          </ul><!--  /list-bullet -->

        </div><!-- /box__content -->
        <footer class="box__footer box__actions">
          <a class="btn btn--primary btn--small btn--narrow" href="#">
            Download .xls
            <span class="icon icon-download icon--button-inline"></span>
          </a>
        </footer>
      </article><!-- /box -->
    </div>

    <div class="grid-col desktop-grid-one-third tablet-grid-one-half">
      <h2 class="delta">Vertically sectioned box</h2>
      <!---
      title: Vertically sectioned box
      usage: This will add top and bottom borders to a box.
      devnotes: >
        Keep in mind vertical spacing and responsiveness as two borders near/
        on top of each other look really awful. This may need to be  combined
        with panels or other means of keeping the distance between elements.
      -->
      <article class="box border-vertical">
        <div class="box__inner box--padded-vertical">
          <header class="box__header">
            <h2 class="delta">
              Contact Details for Business Prices
            </h2>
          </header><!-- /box__header -->

          <div class="box__content">
            <div class="vcard">
               <div class="name">Kat Pegler</div>
               <div class="organisation">Business Prices</div>
               <div class="email"><a href="mailto:ppi@ons.gsi.gov.uk">ppi@ons.gsi.gov.uk</a></div>
               <div class="tel">Telephone: +44 (0)1633 456468</div>
            </div>
          </div><!-- /box__content -->

          <footer class="box__footer">
            <a class="link-complex mini" href="#">
              <span class="link-complex__target box__action__text">View all contacts</span>
              <span class="icon-book" role="presentation"></span>
            </a>
          </footer>
        </div>

      </article><!-- /box -->
    </div>
  </div><!-- /grid-wrap -->
  <div class="grid-wrap">
    <div class="grid-col desktop-grid-one-third tablet-grid-one-half tablet-grid-clear">
      <h2 class="delta">ONS-brand sectioned box</h2>
      <!---
      title: Box with border
      inline: Top border
      usage: >
        The background is usually white, but may also be tinted off-white using the class `.muted`.
      -->
      <article class="box box--padded muted sectioned sectioned-ons-top">
        <div class="box__inner">
          <header class="box__header">
            <h2 class="delta">
              Contact Details for Business Prices
            </h2>
          </header><!-- /box__header -->

          <div class="box__content">
            <div class="vcard">
               <div class="name">Kat Pegler</div>
               <div class="organisation">Business Prices</div>
               <div class="email"><a href="mailto:ppi@ons.gsi.gov.uk">ppi@ons.gsi.gov.uk</a></div>
               <div class="tel">Telephone: +44 (0)1633 456468</div>
            </div>
          </div><!-- /box__content -->

          <footer class="box__footer">
            <a class="link-complex mini" href="#">
              <span class="link-complex__target box__action__text">View all contacts</span>
              <span class="icon-book" role="presentation"></span>
            </a>
          </footer>
        </div>
      </article><!-- /box -->
    </div>
    <div class="grid-col">
      <h2 class="delta">
        Call-out box
      </h2>
      <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. Quod ex, sunt ipsam, at labore aut dicta minima eligendi, eaque veritatis fuga quia nulla delectus voluptates. Ipsum quibusdam ex asperiores nihil.</p>
        <div class="box box--callout">
          <div class="box__content">
            <h2 class="delta flush--half--bottom">This is an explanation box</h2>
            <p>
              Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      <p>Consequatur ipsum natus harum consequuntur in modi, a, pariatur ad praesentium libero minima aperiam, commodi asperiores perspiciatis numquam repudiandae autem nostrum blanditiis maxime nam sunt. Fugiat mollitia doloribus velit enim.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="panel wrapper">
  <div class="grid-wrap">
    <div class="grid-col desktop-grid-one-third  tablet-grid-one-half ">
      <h2 class="delta">Orange box</h2>
      <!---
      title: Orange box
      devnotes: Any anchors and icons will be orange instead of the default blue.
      usage: >
        Normally used to highlight content not directly related to the content
